plates, and frames of reference. It is the baseline and background, a category that orders and values different types of specificity yet remains inherently nonspecific in itself. Across arenas as diverse as city planning, social media, ethnonationalism, and religion, the generic points to spaces in which knowledge is both overproduced and desperately lacking. Moving through ethnographic and historical settings in the Philippines, Europe, and the United States, MacLochlainn reveals how the concept of the generic is crucial to understanding how things repeat, circulate, and are classified in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aChristianityzPhilippines. 0aGeneric, The (Philosophy)xSocial aspectszPhilippines. 0aGeneric, The (Philosophy)xSocial aspects. 0aGeneric, The (Philosophy). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  areligion, ethnonationalism, social media, city planning, elevator music, off-brand, capitalism, consumerism, proprietary, nonfiction, specificity, united states, europe, philippines, unique, copyright, networks, culture, information processing, creativity, originality, sociology, anthropology, generic, open source, reference, intertextuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665090 cprintz978022682275440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226822761423Coveruhtt